children.subject: If you just enroll and take the class P/NP, you might still be able to pass, if there's no set cap on number of lectures you can miss.

I just enrolled in ISF 100A this weekend... it looks like nothing has happened yet, just lectures. There will be pop quizzes at some point and there's a lot of reading I have to catch up on. I'm getting notes from friends in the class.

history.content:
I've emailed multiple professors asking to enroll in their courses (all of which are upper division H/SS), and each of them say that it's too late, despite the class being available for enrollment. 

Does anyone know of any professor/class that would take in a student at this point in the semester? At this point, I'm looking for anything that would satisfy the major requirement.
